To date, the Caatinga comprises a high biodiversity with a high number of endemics (

; 

), and, as other Brazilian biomes, suffers with high levels of degradation due to overexploitation of its natural resources (

).

Among the species mentioned here, the most intriguing is the presence of 

A. buckupi

in a semiarid area. To date, all species of 

Alloniscus

are distributed in coastal areas, except the doubtful 

A. simplex
Schmölzer, 1974

from Aberdare mountains, 
Kenya
(

; 

). The specimens of 

